    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>For small files you can fit in memory,</strong> you can calculate the SHA-512 digest of a file with this code snippet:</p>\n<pre><code>MessageDigest.getInstance(&quot;SHA-512&quot;).digest(Files.readAllBytes(Paths.get(&quot;/path/file.txt&quot;)))\n</code></pre>\n<p>For this code to work you will need JDK7 or higher.</p>\n<p>Note: if the file is too big to fit in memory you should probably go with Guava as proposed.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 465573,
      "reputation" : 200423,
      "user_id" : 869736,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 82,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ae7bb06b9a23a4dd7eea69e853d47d12?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Louis Wasserman",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/869736/louis-wasserman"
    },
    "is_accepted" : true,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1761147314,
    "last_edit_date" : 1761147314,
    "creation_date" : 1438284511,
    "answer_id" : 31732451,
    "question_id" : 31732207,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If third-party libraries are fair game, Guava's <a href=\"http://docs.guava-libraries.googlecode.com/git/javadoc/com/google/common/io/Files.html#hash(java.io.File,%20com.google.common.hash.HashFunction)\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><code>Files.hash</code></a> could make this as simple as</p>\n<pre><code>Files.hash(new File(fileName), Hashing.sha512()).toString();\n</code></pre>\n<p>...which would also potentially be more efficient; if the file is large, it not need be stored in memory all at once as in the <code>Files.readAllBytes</code> solution.  This will also output a proper hash in hexadecimal; if you need it in bytes just use <code>asBytes()</code> instead of <code>toString()</code>.</p>\n<p><strong>UPDATE:</strong> In newer versions of Guava, <code>Files.hash(File,String)</code> has been deprecated. Instead, you can use:</p>\n<pre><code>com.google.common.io.Files.asByteSource(file).hash( Hashing.sha512())\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 15214400,
      "reputation" : 106,
      "user_id" : 11000791,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f5c92943bf0b1a810642e449aac9c6f1?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "TobiasReichert",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11000791/tobiasreichert"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1549628097,
    "creation_date" : 1549628097,
    "answer_id" : 54592270,
    "question_id" : 31732207,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Simplest solution, no external libs, no problems with big files:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static String hashFile(File file)\n        throws NoSuchAlgorithmException, FileNotFoundException, IOException {\n    // Set your algorithm\n    // \"MD2\",\"MD5\",\"SHA\",\"SHA-1\",\"SHA-256\",\"SHA-384\",\"SHA-512\"\n    MessageDigest md = MessageDigest.getInstance(\"SHA-512\");\n    FileInputStream fis = new FileInputStream(file);\n    byte[] dataBytes = new byte[1024];\n\n    int nread = 0;\n    while ((nread = fis.read(dataBytes)) != -1) {\n        md.update(dataBytes, 0, nread);\n    }\n\n    byte[] mdbytes = md.digest();\n\n    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\n    for (int i = 0; i &lt; mdbytes.length; i++) {\n        sb.append(Integer.toString((mdbytes[i] &amp; 0xff) + 0x100, 16).substring(1));\n    }\n    return sb.toString();\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>src: <a href=\"https://www.quora.com/How-do-I-get-the-SHA-256-hash-value-of-a-file-in-Java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.quora.com/How-do-I-get-the-SHA-256-hash-value-of-a-file-in-Java</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14284626,
      "reputation" : 824,
      "user_id" : 10318272,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/2d8FX.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "sdo",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/10318272/sdo"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1588933131,
    "creation_date" : 1588933131,
    "answer_id" : 61676883,
    "question_id" : 31732207,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You could also use Apache Commons Codec.</p>\n\n<p>Maven Repository: <a href=\"https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/commons-codec/commons-codec\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/commons-codec/commons-codec</a></p>\n\n<p>Code example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static String calcSha512Hex(File file) throws FileNotFoundException, IOException {\n    return org.apache.commons.codec.digest.DigestUtils.sha512Hex(new FileInputStream(file));\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
